author: Waylon Galvez
title: TNT rookies struggle
text:
by Waylon Galvez
October 24, 2015 Prized Talk ‘N Text rookies Moala Tautuaa and Troy Rosario vowed to make up for their poor performance during the Tropang Texters’ 114-98 defeat to Alaska late Friday in the Smart Bro Philippine Cup.
It could be rookie jitters and it showed when the 6-7 Tautuaa could only come up with two points, two rebounds and three assists in nearly 20 minutes of play.
“It could have been a rookie jitters or I was unfocused, that’s how I felt,” said Tautuaa. “I don’t want to say rookie jitters and bail myself out. It was just… I wasn’t on my game.”
“I had a hard time adjusting. It was a lot different than the D-League and I couldn’t find my rhythm, I couldn’t find my groove. I struggled everywhere on the floor, and I didn’t feel like myself,’ he said.
Tautuaa, who made electrifying moves during his brief stint with Gilas Pilipinas recently, admits he is still groping for the right form.
“It was a different atmosphere to play in, and adjusting to how the play is here, and that’s how I felt that got me off my groove. For myself, I did feel a little pressure. But the older guys they talked to me and told me I shouldn’t and they just told me to play my game. Today that didn’t come,” he added.
Rosario, the No. 2 pick originally by Mahindra but was obtained in a preseason trade, had a similarly unimpressive debut with just four points and three rebounds in more than 15 minutes of play.
